# Custody Request (مكوث) Workflow Redesign – Point 7

Point 7 requires an **automated, system-mediated** workflow between the two parents. The system ("court" in the requirement refers to the system acting as the mediator) handles forwarding and tracking.

```
Non-Custodial Parent → System → Custodial Parent → System → Non-Custodial Parent
```

**Court Role:**
1. **Visibility**: Court staff can view all requests and their current state (Approved/Rejected/Waiting).
2. **Automated Escalation**: If the custodial parent rejects multiple subsequent requests (e.g., 3 in a row), the system will automatically trigger a violation/obligation alert to the parent, and suggest actions for the court staff (e.g., "Review custody arrangement due to repeated denial of visitation/stay").

---

## Current vs. Target Flow

| Step | Current | Target |
|------|---------|--------|
| 1 | Father creates request | Non-custodial parent creates request |
| 2 | Court approves/rejects ❌ | **System automatically notifies** custodial parent |
| 3 | — | **Custodial parent** accepts or rejects (with reason) |
| 4 | — | **System** records the reaction and notifies the non-custodial parent |
| 5 | — | If custodial parent rejects **multiple times**, system auto-sends an **Obligation Alert** and notifies the Court |
| 6 | — | Court staff views **full history** of all requests and reactions |

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Threshold Question**: How many consecutive rejections should trigger the automated violation alert? The plan currently assumes **3 consecutive rejections**.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Breaking Change**: The [ProcessCustodyRequest](file:///c:/Users/Mhamed/source/repos/wesal-backend/src/Wesal.Presentation/CustodyRequests/ProcessCustodyRequest.cs#14-43) endpoint (currently used by court to approve/reject) will be **deleted**. The court no longer directly decides on requests.

