## Workflow Diagram

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> WaitingForResponse : Non-custodial parent creates request\n(system auto-notifies custodial parent)
    WaitingForResponse --> Approved : Custodial parent accepts
    WaitingForResponse --> Rejected : Custodial parent rejects\n(with reason)
    Approved --> [*] : Non-custodial parent notified ✅
    Rejected --> [*] : Non-custodial parent notified ❌
    
    note right of Rejected
        If N consecutive rejections:
        1. ObligationAlert sent to parent
        2. Case alert sent to Court Staff
    end note
```

---

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification (via Swagger/Postman)
1. Create custody request as non-custodial parent → verify `WaitingForResponse` + custodial parent gets notification
2. Respond as custodial parent (accept) → verify [Approved](file:///c:/Users/Mhamed/source/repos/wesal-backend/src/Wesal.Domain/Entities/Notifications/NotificationTemplate.cs#16-22) + non-custodial parent gets notification
3. Respond as custodial parent (reject) 3 times sequentially:
   - Request 1: Rejected
   - Request 2: Rejected
   - Request 3: Rejected → Verify the handler correctly identifies the streak, and issues the [ObligationAlert](file:///c:/Users/Mhamed/source/repos/wesal-backend/src/Wesal.Domain/Entities/Notifications/NotificationTemplate.cs#105-111) to the parent and the suggestion alert to the court.
4. Verify court staff can call [ListCustodyRequests](file:///c:/Users/Mhamed/source/repos/wesal-backend/src/Wesal.Application/CustodyRequests/ListCustodyRequests/ListCustodyRequestsQueryHandler.cs#15-126) and see the new `ResponseNote` and history perfectly format.
